<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>TSI 05-47-03 - Certain RE 200 and RE 300 Bus Models Built Between March 1, 2004 and February 27, 2005 May
        Require an Additional Support Bracket for the Radiator Surge Tank
    </stitle>
    <tsi id="tsi054703" tsitype="truck">
        <tsinumber>05-47-03</tsinumber>
        <tsidate>December, 2005</tsidate>
        <subjectfile>BUS BODY</subjectfile>
        <subjectgroup>
            <subject>Certain RE 200 and RE 300 Bus Models Built Between March 1, 2004 and February 27, 2005 May Require
                an Additional Support Bracket for the Radiator Surge Tank
            </subject>
        </subjectgroup>
        <distribution dealer="yes" fleet="yes" bodybuilder="no" isis_cd="yes"/>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>RE 200
                    <daterange>
                        <startdate>03/01/2004</startdate>
                        <enddate>02/27/2005</enddate>
                    </daterange>
                </truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>RE 300
                    <daterange>
                        <startdate>03/01/2004</startdate>
                        <enddate>02/27/2005</enddate>
                    </daterange>
                </truckmodel>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>The surge tank mounting in RE 200 and RE 300 bus models built between March 1, 2004 and February
                    27, 2005 may loosen and vibrate. A service kit is now available with the necessary parts and
                    instructions to add a support bracket to reinforce the surge tank mounting.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
        <partsinfo>
            <table id="t0547031">
                <tgroup cols="3" align="center">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="0.82*"/>
                    <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="1.60*"/>
                    <colspec colname="col3" colwidth="0.58*"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Part Number</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Description</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Quantity</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>2589326C91</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Surge Tank Support Kit: 2211553C1, Instructions (1)2211533C1, Support Bracket
                                    (!)310427R1 Bolt (1)472399C1, Self Tapping Screw (4)428105001, Flat Washer
                                    (1)417138001, Nut (1)
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>1</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </partsinfo>
        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="1">
            <title>Service procedure</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid property damage, personal injury, or death, park the vehicle on a flat level surface,
                        set the parking brake, turn the engine off, and chock the wheels.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <para>Using the surge tank as a guide, position the lower bracket (Figure 1, Item 1) between the surge tank
                and side wall of the vehicle. Attach the lower bracket to the lower mounting hole in the surge tank
                (Figure 1, Item 2) with a fastener from the kit.
            </para>
            <para>Place the bracket against the tubing and drill four (4) 1/4 inch holes for fasteners. Install the
                fasteners from the kit and tighten to 10 to 15 Lbf-ft (14 to 20 Nm).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0547031" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/g0547031.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitheight="408px"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. Kit Instructions</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Lower Bracket</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Lower Surge Tank Mounting Hole</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. Mounting Fasteners (4)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
    </tsi>
</isis>
